        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 5:04PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 504 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Sardis, or 17 miles north of Savannah, moving north at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Parsons, Decaturville, Montgomery, Thurman, Lick Skillet,
Wilkinstown, Haney, Pleasant Grove, Bath Springs, Mount Tabor,
Garrett, Beacon, Red Walnut, Largo, Dunbar, and Mount Lebanon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
